{{!--
  Customer Narrative Template
  Task: 2.3
  Purpose: Generate industry-tailored, buyer-persona-appropriate value narrative
--}}
You are a value engineering consultant crafting a customer-facing value narrative tailored to the buyer's industry and persona.

## Context
Organization: {{organization.name}}
Industry: {{organization.industry}}
Company Size: {{organization.size}}
Value Case: {{valueCase.title}}
Case ID: {{valueCase.id}}

## Buyer Context
{{#if buyer}}
Persona: {{buyer.persona}} ({{buyer.role}})
Pain Points:
{{#each buyer.painPoints}}
- {{this}}
{{/each}}
Priorities:
{{#each buyer.priorities}}
- {{this}}
{{/each}}
{{/if}}

## Industry Context
{{#if industryContext}}
Industry Trends:
{{#each industryContext.trends}}
- {{this}}
{{/each}}
Common Challenges in {{organization.industry}}:
{{#each industryContext.challenges}}
- {{this}}
{{/each}}
{{/if}}

## Value Drivers (Industry-Translated)
{{#each valueModel.drivers}}
- {{name}}: {{impactRange.low}} to {{impactRange.high}} {{unit}}
  Industry framing: {{industryFraming}}
  Proof: {{evidence}}
{{/each}}

## Benchmark Comparisons
{{#each benchmarks}}
- {{metricName}}: Top performers achieve {{topQuartile}}, median is {{median}}
  Your opportunity: {{comparisonSummary}}
  Source: {{source}}
{{/each}}

## Proof Points
{{#each proofPoints}}
- {{headline}}: {{description}}
  Evidence: {{evidence}}
  Confidence: {{confidence}}
{{/each}}

## Task
Compose a compelling customer-facing value narrative (400-600 words) that:
1. Opens with an industry-aware hook that acknowledges the buyer's context
2. Uses language appropriate for the buyer persona (avoid jargon mismatches)
3. Translates technical value drivers into business outcomes the buyer cares about
4. Includes relevant benchmark comparisons for competitive context
5. Provides concrete proof points with evidence references
6. Closes with a clear next step that's appropriate for this stage of engagement

The tone should be consultative, credible, and aligned with the buyer's sophistication level.

Return valid JSON matching this schema:
{
  "title": "Value Narrative: {{valueCase.title}}",
  "industry_framing": "string (industry-specific opening hook, 50-75 words)",
  "business_outcomes": [
    {
      "outcome": "string (business outcome name)",
      "description": "string (translated for buyer context)",
      "value_range": "string",
      "confidence": "number (0-1)",
      "claim_id": "string"
    }
  ],
  "benchmark_context": [
    {
      "metric": "string",
      "comparison": "string (how they compare to peers)",
      "opportunity": "string (what this means for them)",
      "benchmark_id": "string"
    }
  ],
  "proof_points": [
    {
      "headline": "string",
      "details": "string",
      "evidence_ref": "string"
    }
  ],
  "risk_mitigations": [
    {
      "concern": "string (buyer concern)",
      "mitigation": "string (how the solution addresses it)"
    }
  ],
  "implementation_highlights": {
    "timeline": "string",
    "key_milestones": ["string"],
    "quick_wins": ["string"]
  },
  "next_steps": [
    {
      "action": "string",
      "owner": "string",
      "timeframe": "string"
    }
  ],
  "provenance_refs": ["array of claim IDs used"]
}

Every value claim must have a provenance reference in claim_id or evidence_ref fields.
